citations:
    citation-adwd-a-ghost-in-winterfell:
        source: source-adwd
        properties:
            locator: "A Ghost in Winterfell"
            text_from_source: "You prayed, and the gods sent us. You want to die as Theon? We'll give you that. A nice quick death, 'twill hardly hurt at all. But not till you've sung for Abel. He's waiting for you."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Theon POV. Continued snowstorm. Yellow Dick found dead with his own severed member stuffed in his mouth. Stable collapses, 26 horses and 2 grooms die. Little Walder's murder discovery hinted later; tensions between Freys and Manderlys. Theon prays at the weirwood, the tree seems to whisper his name. The spearwives Rowan, Holly, and an unnamed third reveal themselves — they work for Abel/Mance Rayder. Theon realizes they are the killers."
